      "latex": "",
      "raw": "For a general ratio a:b (drawing : real), the scale factor k that converts a real length L_real to a drawing length L_draw is: $$ k = \\frac{a}{b} $$ $$ L_{\\mathrm{draw}} = L_{\\mathrm{real}} \\cdot k = L_{\\mathrm{real}} \\cdot \\frac{a}{b} $$ Conversely: $$ L_{\\mathrm{real}} = \\frac{L_{\\mathrm{draw}}}{k} = L_{\\mathrm{draw}} \\cdot \\frac{b}{a} $$ To normalize any ratio a:b to 1:n: $$ n = \\frac{b}{a} \\quad\\Rightarrow\\quad 1:n $$ Print percentage to convert from scale a₁:b₁ to a₂:b₂: $$ \\text{Print \\%} = 100 \\times \\frac{a_2/b_2}{a_1/b_1} = 100 \\times \\frac{a_2 \\cdot b_1}{b_2 \\cdot a_1} $$ When deriving a scale from two measurements: $$ k = \\frac{L_{\\mathrm{draw}}}{L_{\\mathrm{real}}} \\quad\\Rightarrow\\quad 1:\\frac{1}{k} $$"
